<p style="text-indent: 0;">EEThomas Knox</p>
</div>
<div class="docback">
<div class="note-source" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0272-sn">

   <p>
<abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Letter Book Copy: letters copied into a bound letter-book ]">LB</abbr>, <span class="ref-rep" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ U.S. Library of Congress, George Washington Papers, Washington, D.C. ]">DLC:GW</span>.
 The letter-book copy is in GWs hand. The running totals have been omitted.</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0272-fn-0001-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0272-fn-0001">1</a>

   <p>A pattipan was a small tin pan for baking pies.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0272-fn-0002-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0272-fn-0002">2</a>

   <p>A slop basin in a tea set was a bowl used for tea dregs.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0272-fn-0003-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0272-fn-0003">3</a>

   <p>Osnaburg was a strong cotton fabric used for work clothing for slaves. A truss was a bundle or a pack.</p>

</div>
<div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#GEWN-02-04-02-0272-fn-0004-ptr" id="GEWN-02-04-02-0272-fn-0004">4</a>

   <p>Roll was a fine-twilled English melton wool fabric.</p>

</div>
